{"type":null,"faqId":36226,"title":"My phone often disconnects from the Wi-Fi network on its own","answer":"<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>After successfully connecting to the Wi-Fi network, keep the\nphone within range of the Wi-Fi hotspot to avoid losing the connection due to a\nweak signal.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>For EMUI 2.0 and EMUI 2.3, select <b>Wi-Fi</b> in the <b>Settings</b>\npage to enter the Wi-Fi settings. Open the options menu, select <b>Advanced &gt; Keep Wi-Fi on during sleep</b>\nand then select <b>Always</b>. The phone\nwill always stay connected to the Wi-Fi network.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>For EMUI 3.0, select <b>Wi-Fi</b>\nin the <b>Settings</b> page to enter the\nWi-Fi settings. Select <b>Advanced settings\n&gt; Keep Wi-Fi on during sleep</b> and then select <b>Always</b>. The phone will always stay connected to the Wi-Fi network.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span>If the problem persists,\nturn off the Wi-Fi function and then turn it back on or restart the Wi-Fi\nhotspot.</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"1251","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"1","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1438759620000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":40,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Wi-Fi, wireless network, connect to Wi-Fi","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}